Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper primarily focuses on analyzing and designing computer communication networks, which falls under the scope of this sub-category. 
2. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper discusses key graph theory concepts used to represent different types of networks, which is a fundamental topic in data structures and algorithms. 
3. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper mentions studying various types of networks, including the Internet, WANs, LANs, and networking protocols, which are all relevant to this sub-category. 
4. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses modeling networks to investigate problems related to network protocols, which involves information theory concepts such as coding and compression. 
5. cs.CC (Computational Complexity) - The paper briefly mentions some of the tools used to generate graphs for representing practical networks, which may involve computational complexity considerations.
